t">The Case against a Free School in Stoke Poges</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Ministry of Education hid the planning of this school from the residents of the village for years, and cannot explain  on what grounds, until there was no significant time to appeal, and then we find that there is no appeal process</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is a surfeit of Secondary School places in the Bucks Educational Authority and, therefore, no demand for school places or a free school in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the VILLAGE of Stoke Poges</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is no Local demand (a key tenant of the Free school ethos) a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ll demand </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for a Sikh school </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is from remote boroughs, Slough, Ealing, Southall etc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">., contrary to “Free Schools in 2014 – How to Apply”, para 1.2 and  Evidence of Demand P23 para 6.16 Box E1</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This is not the deprived urban area where Free schools were supposed to be created to save neighbourhoods</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and children </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">from failing schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  This is a village not a failing urban area.</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Local schools are very good and do not need “rescuing”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and are not underachieving</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">No real consultation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> conducted, as required by the Free Schools in 2014 process,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">school except with its own (remote) community</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">What consultation was conducted was done so fraudulently</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (multiple uses of same copied letter etc) </span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Planning permission was going to be declined but submission “pulled” when its imminent failure was known (by Govt. representatives advising the school) and new laws circumvented local Council </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">planning </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">decisions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for a year</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (no Localism locally)</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">One year planning bypass will lead to “dog in a manger” attitude and emotional blackmail using pupils who have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">studied here for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a year and who will, properly and under current rules, be displaced as the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">temporary planning law “bypass” is closed and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">school moves</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to a new venue</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Public funds squandered on the purchase, reportedly “over market value” </span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Slough Council have sold off all assets and cannot now provide school places as required</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> yet will knock down purpose built school to build a football pitch </span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The proposed free school will teach no religion other than that of the Sikh faith, “I believe that any school, free or otherwise that fails to teach an understanding of, and a respect for, other ways of life is a failing school and should be treated as such” Lord Singh Director of the Network of Sikh Organisations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Radio 4, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Tuesday 23 Oct 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, 07:46</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This organisation has no intention of meeting the mix of selected faith/other faith ratio as required</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Stoke Poges is a VILLAGE.  Residents number approx. 5,000, the school aims to educate and employ upto 1,000 people arriving and leaving daily – our infrastructure is unable to accommodate this, which is why planning application was rejected</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The proposed Free School will not confirm that it will not operate from its premises on weekends for weddings and other social functions.  This level of obfuscation is deplorable and typical of this school’s attitude to planners, residents, legal process.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 7.5pt 36pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span